ght{} 				\textbackslash usepackage\textbraceleft mathrsfs\textbraceright{} 				\textbackslash usepackage\textbraceleft upgreek\textbraceright{} 				\textbackslash setlength\textbraceleft\textbackslash oddsidemargin\textbraceright\textbraceleft -69pt\textbraceright{} 				\textbackslash begin\textbraceleft document\textbraceright\$\$-\$\$\textbackslash end\textbraceleft document\textbraceright -3.5. We further establish that fine-tuning is preferable to few-shot training with a relatively modest quantity of annotated text. Our findings show that fine-tuned open-source LLMs can be effectively deployed in a broad spectrum of text annotation applications. We provide a Python notebook facilitating the application of LLMs in text annotation for other researchers.},
  pmcid = {PMC11655591},
  pmid = {39712076},
  file = {C:\Users\jupf0\Zotero\storage\EILFBTT6\Alizadeh et al. - 2025 - Open-source LLMs for text annotation a practical guide for model setting and fine-tuning.pdf}
